UK-based rapper Olukayode Odesanya aka Kida Kudz has revealed he has been suffering depression for two years “nonstop”. Kida Kudz made this known in a series of posts on micro-blogging app, Twitter. The 26-year-old rose to fame at 15 after winning the second edition of the Peak Talent Show in 2010. According to the father of two, in a now-deleted tweet, he’s tired of fighting every day in a world where no one cares. He, however, reached out for help, seeking therapy in another post. - Advertisement - In an additional post, he expressed relief after his initial tweets attracted reactions from his fans.   9ice, wife welcome new child     Adekunle Gold releases much anticipated album     How to know if you’re a side chick/ guy, by Morey Faith   He subsequently urged his fans to stay happy no matter the condition they pass through. The tweets read: “Been suffering from depression for two years none stop (sic). I’m putting myself out there God. Heal me. “Any therapist memberz out here? Get in contact pls. “Tired of fighting myself every day in dis cold world that no one gives a f**k. I’m standing strong still but I’m tired yo. “This might make me pu**y but I would rather share with you guys the same people that I drop music for. “I’m going to cry all day. “Im good you guys . Feel better abit after Letting that out. “No matter the condition you gotta stay jiggy.”